            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <p>
                      <strong><em>So who is this "Maggie" person, anyway?</em></strong><br><br>
                      My education and background is in cognitive science and user experience research. I wanted to have a more impactful role in consumer-facing products, so I started learning web development in December, 2013. <br><br>
              				When I'm not typing furiously on my computer, I like to go hiking, camping, skiing, and all manner of outdoorsy things. I'm more of a cat person than a dog person. I lived in Italy for a couple of years. I'm a Star Trek fan, a Kim Stanley Robinson fan, and yes, I loved the movie <%= link_to "Her (2013)", "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1798709/", target: "_blank"%>.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <p>
              				<strong><em>I'm educated.</em></strong><br><br>
              				I got my BA from the University of Chicago in 2010 and my MSc from l'Universit√† degli studi di Trento in 2012. While I was at these prestigious institutions, I did a lot of research around the subject of language and communication. I wrote my master's thesis on <%= link_to "communication via signaling games", "https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B6EjfMEqe_MjM1ZUS3FoMFFLVlk/edit?usp=sharing", target: "_blank"%>.<br><br>
              				I love learning, and I constantly take courses on <%= link_to "Coursera", "https://www.coursera.org/user/i/62da43c330791faf1444ba89f764e988", target: "_blank"%> and <%= link_to "Udacity", "https://www.udacity.com/", target: "_blank"%>.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4">
                    <p>
              				<strong><em>I'm skilled.</em></strong><br><br>
                      I'm primarily a <%= link_to "Ruby on Rails", "http://rubyonrails.org/", target: "_blank" %> web developer, but I've also dabbled in <%= link_to "Google App Engine", "https://developers.google.com/appengine/?csw=1", target: "_blank" %> (with Python and webapp2). I'm rather new to the field, so expounding on any supposed expertise would be pure bluff. But I have come to web development brandishing my love of learning, so I hope to start putting technical feathers in my hat soon.<br><br>
              				From my research background, I have a good knowledge base of statistical tools and scientific research methods. In the field of user experience research, work that I've done has included light-weight UI testing, lean UX, survey design (both online and mobile, large and small scale), A/B testing, and focus groups.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
